org.jlokalize
Class LanguageTreeProject

java.lang.Object
  org.jlokalize.LanguageTreeProject

public class LanguageTreeProject
extends java.lang.Object

A complete project description. Each project has: - a directory - a base identifier (file name syntax is directory/base_languagecodes.extension) - a TreeNode holding the data And we can change the base and directory as well as loading the data from files, saving to files or creating new empty projects.

open

public boolean open(java.io.File file)
Given a file from a project, searches for all files that match a certain regular expression (base at the beginning, then arbitrary stuff, then the extension at the end). Then obtains the language codes from the middle part of the file name (language, country, variant) and inserts a node in a newly created tree according to the language codes, automatically adding all missing nodes.

Parameters:
file - One of the files from the project (doesn't matter which one).
Returns:
True if opening was successful.

rebase

Chzanges the base for all nodes of the project. Used by the 'save as' menu.

Parameters:
file - The file to extract the base from.

save

public void save()
Traverse through the nodes list and saves the languages to a file whos name is derived from directory, base and toFileName() from LanguageProperties.
